# Plan: plot all `vehicle_angular_velocity` instances + resolve device names

## Context
`analyze_imu_vibration.py` produces vibration/failure-mode plots from a PX4 ULog.
Two of its plots cover `vehicle_angular_velocity` (the filtered angular rate the
rate controller runs on). The airframe in question publishes **3**
`vehicle_angular_velocity` instances (one per IMU — a custom build; stock PX4
publishes only the single selected gyro), but both functions currently call
`get_topic(ulog, "vehicle_angular_velocity")`, which returns only instance 0. So
two of the three gyros' filtered rates are never plotted.

Additionally, the user wants each instance labeled with the **device name** of its
gyro. The `vehicle_angular_velocity` topic carries no `device_id` field (only
`timestamp`, `timestamp_sample`, `xyz[]`, `xyz_derivative[]` — confirmed against a
real log), so device identity must be resolved indirectly.

Outcome: both plots cover all instances, each labeled with its decoded gyro chip
name (e.g. `ICM20602`).

